data.title: LibGuides at Jet Propulsion Laboratory
data.meta_description: LibGuides: Subject Resources: Women in STEM: EBooks
data.text:
Library staff can provide customized lists by topics. All books can be accessed and downloaded from within the JPL network. They can then be transferred to mobile devices for later reading. Our licenses with publishers prohibits redistribution, so if you would like to recommend books to your colleagues, please ask them to download their own copies.

Building A New Leadership Ladder: Transforming Male-Dominated Organizations to Support Women on the Rise, 2023

Her Space, Her Time: How Trailblazing Women Scientists Decoded the Hidden Universe, 2023

Presumed Incompetent II: Race, Class, Power, and Resistance of Women in Academia, 2020

Women in Aerospace Materials: Advancement and Perspectives of Emerging Technologies, 2020

Women in Industrial and Systems Engineering, 2020

Women in Microelectronics, 2020

Women in Nanotechnology: Contributions from the Atomic Level and Up, 2020

The Development of Women and Young Professionals in STEM Careers: Tips and Tricks, 2019

Find Your Path: Unconventional Lessons from 36 Leading Scientists and Engineers, 2019

(Not) Getting Paid to Do What You Love: Gender, Social Media, and Aspirational Work, 2017

Gender, Technology and the New Woman, 2017
